NEW YORK, NY – OCTOBER 28: Curtis “50 Cent” Jackson attends the world premiere of ‘Nobody’s Fool’ at AMC Lincoln Square Theater on October 28, 2018 in New York, New York. (Photo by Roy Rochlin/Getty Images for Paramount Pictures) Curtis Jackson, better known as 50 Cent is ready to impart his wisdom with his upcoming book “Hustle Harder, Hustle Smarter”. As he enjoys the fruits of his ever-growing television empire while also keeping the Instagram feed immeasurably spicy, the Get Rich Or Die Tryin rapper has deemed it due time to impart his wisdom upon us. The rapper has announced that Enter Hustle Harder, Hustle Smarter, his first book since teaming with Robert Greene for The 50th Law in 2009, will be released on April 28. “I’ve had my share of setbacks, but I knew that I was never gonna stay there long,” he tweeted, revealing both the cover and release date. Hustle Harder, Hustle Smarter by 50 Cent | Photo: Twitter/50Cent It’s unclear as to how much time will be spent reflecting on his music career, but with this book hyped as “self-help” rather than biography, it appears this is more of a guidebook on the key principles of hustle and enough personal anecdotes to keep his fanbase entertained. The official Hustle Harder, Hustle Smarter description reads as follows: “For the first time, Curtis “50 Cent” Jackson opens up about his amazing comeback—from tragic personal loss to thriving businessman and cable’s highest-paid executive—in this unique self-help guide, his first since his blockbuster New York Times bestseller The 50th Law.”